Olaide Oyelude, Katsina The police in Katsina State have arrested a 24-year-old man, Mohammed Sani, for being in possession of a vehicle suspected to have been stolen. The vehicle is a silver Toyota Camry 2008 model with Delta State number plate, KWC 32 AH. Spokesman for the Katsina State Police Command, SP Gambo Isah, who confirmed the development, in Katsina on Tuesday, said Sani, a resident of the Dei-Dei area of Abuja, was arrested on Sunday in Dabai village, Dabai Local Government Area of the state. Isah said the car was allegedly snatched at gunpoint from its owner in Abuja, adding that the suspect wanted to take it across the Nigeria/Niger Republic border through Katsina State. The police spokesman stated, “On November 3, 2019, around 10.26am, based on a tip-off, the command succeeded in arresting one Mohammed Sani, 24, of Dei-Dei, FCT, Abuja, in possession of a stolen Toyota Camry, 2008 model with Delta State number plate KWC 32 AH at the Dabai village, Danja Local Government Area of Katsina State. “The said vehicle belongs to one Amao Livingstone of Dove Resort, Mabushi, Abuja, and was snatched at gunpoint on November 2, 2019, around 11pm in the Mabushi area of Abuja. “Nemesis caught up with the said suspect when he drove the said vehicle to Katsina State with the aim of transiting through the Nigerian-Niger border. “The suspect is assisting the police in their investigation.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 